倒气氛或取消文化战争，但总比没有好。</p><p>首先，也是最重要的是，拜登可能会采取更多措施来对抗通胀，并使美联储开始降息。</p><h4>拜登如何解决通货膨胀和利率问题</h4><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/what-do-americans-want-that-biden">阅读更多</a></p>; 
Don't be a decelTechnological progress must be harnessed, not fought https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/dont-be-a-decel https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/dont-be-a-decelNoah Smith Wed, 04 Oct 2023 03:55:56 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg" width="712" height="445" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:600,&quot;width&quot;:960,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:712,&quot;bytes&quot;:108946,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F4e8676af-58b4-42ee-99a8-e545a4b3e28a_960x600.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></figure></div><p> “Decel”是<a href="https://effectiveaccelerationism.substack.com/p/repost-effective-accelerationism">e/acc 社区</a>使用的贬义俚语。它是“减速主义者”的缩写，意思是那些想要减缓技术进步的人。大多数减速者可能不会明确地以这种方式看待自己，但他们的态度和信念最终会朝这个方向发展。</p><p>例如，考虑疫苗。本周，<a href="https://www.nobelprize.org/prizes/medicine/2023/press-release/">诺贝尔医学奖</a>授予了发明 mRNA 疫苗的 Katalin Karikó 和 Drew Weissman。迄今为止，卡里科和韦斯曼发明的技术除了在全球范围内<a href="https://www.commonwealthfund.org/blog/2022/two-years-covid-vaccines-prevented-millions-deaths-hospitalizations">拯救了数百万人</a>的<a href="https://www.thelancet.com/journals/laninf/article/PIIS1473-3099(22)00320-6/fulltext">生命</a>外，还被用来制造针对从<a href="https://www.mskcc.org/news/can-mrna-vaccines-fight-pancreatic-cancer-msk-clinical-researchers-are-trying-find-out">胰腺癌</a>到<a href="https://www.news-medical.net/news/20230720/New-mRNA-based-malaria-vaccine-shows-promise-in-preclinical-trials.aspx">疟疾</a>等各种疾病的疫苗。请记住，胰腺癌是一种无声杀手——很难被发现，当您知道自己患有这种癌症时，您可能已经死了。与此同时，疟疾是人类最具破坏性的地方病之一，每年在全世界夺走<a href="https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/malaria">数十万人的</a>生命。</p><p>这对于人类科学和技术来说是一个令人难以置信的胜利——不仅对于创造疫苗的研究人员来说，而且对于支持他们工作的机构来说也是如此。其中包括<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC9975718/">资助这项研究的</a>NIH，以及对 Moderna 和 BioNTech 等公司进行高瞻远瞩的风险投资家。其中包括特朗普政府的“曲速行动”，该行动成功地<a href="https://www.aamc.org/news/covid-19-vaccines-were-developed-record-time-can-we-make-future-vaccines-even-faster">在创纪录的时间内</a>开发出了一种新型疫苗，证明了 mRNA 疫苗的有用性，并为未来的公私合作提供了典范。它包括能够以令人难以置信的规模大规模生产 mRNA 疫苗的整个制造商链。</p><p>在过去，这种胜利会激发全国人民的感激之情和自豪感，就像研制出脊髓灰质炎疫苗时那样。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1d31e53c-70e3-4d81-908f-1812f80cb45f_318x403.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1d31e53c-70e3-4d81-908f-1812f80cb45f_318x403.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1d31e53c-70e3-4d81-908f-1812f80cb45f_318x403.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1d31e53c-70e3-4d81-908f-1812f80c